OL,7,FA tribute from the his squadron
OL,8,Fdescribed Cpl Gill as a "loving and
OL,9,Fdoting father, husband, and son" as
OL,10,Fwell as a "much-loved and respected
OL,11,Fleader."
OL,13,FCommanding Officer 4th Battalion, The
OL,14,FRanger Regiment, Lieutenant Colonel
OL,15,FCharles Bairsto said: "Cpl Chris
OL,16,F'Gilly' Gill was a remarkable Army
OL,17,FSpecial Operations soldier. A strong
OL,18,Fand natural leader, he truly lived the
OL,19,FRANGER ethos.
