OL,3,CBritish Army pays tribute to soldier
OL,4,Cafter death in 'non-operational
OL,5,Cincident'
OL,7,F"Promptly selected to attend the
OL,8,FSection Commanders' Battle Course, he
OL,9,Fexcelled in honing his skills in an
OL,10,Farduous and taxing environment,
OL,11,Fdeveloping his leadership under
OL,12,Fpressure. His talent quickly led to
OL,13,Fpromotion to Corporal.
OL,15,F"He deployed soon after to Mazar-i-
OL,16,FSharif, Afghanistan, where leading a
OL,17,Fsmall, close-knit team, he delivered
OL,18,Ftraining to specialist partners.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/9
