OL,3,CBritish Army pays tribute to soldier
OL,4,Cafter death in 'non-operational
OL,5,Cincident'
OL,7,F"His professionalism again earmarked
OL,8,Fhim for further commitments going on
OL,9,Fto partner local forces in Belize, the
OL,10,FUS, Kenya and Morocco. Throughout, his
OL,11,Fassured approach, knowledge and humour
OL,12,Fwon the respect and loyalty of
OL,13,Fpartnered forces, making him a
OL,14,Fremarkably successful instructor.
OL,16,F"His relentless, quick wit became
OL,17,Fcentral to the morale of the teams he
OL,18,Fled. In the face of adversity, he
OL,19,Fcould always be relied upon to get
OL,20,Feveryone chuckling no matter the
OL,21,Fsituation.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/9
