OL,3,CBritish Army pays tribute to soldier
OL,4,Cafter death in 'non-operational
OL,5,Cincident'
OL,7,F"The death of Cpl Gill is sorely felt.
OL,8,FHis family have lost a loving and
OL,9,Fdoting father, husband, and son. His
OL,10,Ffriends and fellow Rangers will miss a
OL,11,Fmuch-loved and respected leader.
OL,13,F"The Army has lost a professional,
OL,14,Fcapable, and loyal Special Operations
OL,15,Fsoldier, whose contribution to the
OL,16,Fteam made it much stronger than the
OL,17,Fsum of its parts; he made a real
OL,18,Fimpact throughout his distinguished
OL,19,Fcareer."
